"script": "What if the paper stamped \"this is not a bill\" is hiding money you should question? After every medical visit, your insurer mails an E O B \u2014 an Explanation of Benefits. It lists three numbers per service: provider charge, allowed amount, and what you actually owe. If the bill you get later asks more than the E O B's allowed amount, that gap is yours to question. Snap both papers into a free A I \u2014 it lines them up side by side and circles any mismatch. Stop throwing it out. Read the gap.",
